DUBAI - South Africa have four batsmen in the top 10 of the ICC ODI Player Rankings according to the International Cricket Council (ICC) on Monday. AB De Villiers is in second place behind India’s Virat Kohli. The remaining three SA top-tenners are Quinton de Kock (6),  Faf du Plessis (8) and Hashim Amla (9). READ: Australia reclaim Ashes with innings and 41-run win at WACA On the bowling standings, SA’s Pakistan-born spinner Imran Tahir is in second place behind Hasan Ali, Pakistan’s medium-fast paceman. Kagiso Rabada, in 5th position, is the only other SA bowler in the top 10 rankings. World’s top 10 batsmen: 1 Virat Kohli (Ind)
